**Simple Past Tense**. The [simple past tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/simple_past_tense.htm) is used to describe a completed activity that happened in the past.

![][image1]

**Past Progressive Tense**. The [past progressive tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/past_progressive_tense.htm) is used to describe an ongoing activity in the past. Often, it is used to set the scene for another action.

![][image2]

**Past Perfect Tense**. The [past perfect tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/past_perfect_tense.htm) is used to emphasize that an action was completed before another took place.

![][image3]

**Past Perfect Progressive Tense**. The [past perfect progressive tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/past_perfect_progressive_tense.htm) is used to show that an ongoing action in the past has ended.

![][image4]

**Simple Present Tense**. The [simple present tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/simple_present_tense.htm) is mostly used to describe facts and habits.

![][image5]

**Present Progressive Tense**. The [present progressive tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/present_progressive_tense.htm) is used for an ongoing action in the present.

![][image6]

**Present Perfect Tense**. The [present perfect tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/present_perfect_tense.htm) is used for actions began in the past. (Often, the actions continue into the present.)

![][image7]

**Present Perfect Progressive Tense**. The [present perfect progressive tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/present_perfect_progressive_tense.htm) is used for a continuous activity that began in the past and continues into the present, or a continuous activity that began in past but has now finished (usually very recently).

![][image8]

**Simple Future Tense**. The [simple future tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/simple_future_tense.htm) is used for an action that will occur in the future.

![][image9]

**Future Progressive Tense**. The [future progressive tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/future_progressive_tense.htm) is used for an ongoing action that will occur in the future.

![][image10]

**Future Perfect Tense**. The [future perfect tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/future_perfect_tense.htm) is used to describe an action that will have been completed at some point in the future.

![][image11]

**Future Perfect Progressive Tense**. The [future perfect progressive tense](https://www.grammar-monster.com/glossary/future_perfect_progressive_tense.htm) is used for an ongoing action that will be completed at some specified time in the future.

![][image12]
